# Private / AI-agent files — keep off GitHub
# NOTE: CLAUDE.md and rules/ are intentionally tracked — the test gate reads them
# (test-count / Protocol 38 / Protocol 40 guards), so they must stay in the repo.
.claude/

# Claude-facing local reference library (BRAIN_DUMP.md et al.) — local-only, never
# committed. It reconstructs a session's understanding from disk on the owner's PC;
# it is NOT for the phone (that is QUEUE.md, which IS committed). See CLAUDE.md's
# pointer index. library/MANIFEST.txt is the one committed exception — a filename-only
# manifest (Protocol 46 / Suite 220) so the doc-reference-integrity gate can check
# pointer paths against it even on a clean CI checkout where library/ doesn't exist.
library/*
!library/MANIFEST.txt

# Dependencies
node_modules/

# Build output
dist/
_site/
dist-staging/

# OS files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# IDE
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

# Repomix output (generated artifact — never committed)
repomix-output.*

# CI failure-evidence (Health-batch U4) — screenshots + console/gate logs written
# ONLY when a check fails, uploaded by the CI workflow, then swept (Protocol 41).
# Never committed.
test-artifacts/

# Logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*

# Local planning artifacts — never committed/pushed/deployed
# These are AI-agent research and design docs generated during the planning chain.
# They live in planning/ (the whole folder is ignored); the filename patterns
# below stay as a belt-and-suspenders guard in case any are kept/created elsewhere.
planning/
MASTER_PLAN.md
PARALLELIZATION_PLAN.md
HOUSE_STANDARD.md
DETERMINISTIC_FEATURES.md
*_AUDIT.md
*_SLATE.md
*_DESIGN.md
